<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« | <span style="text-decoration: underline;">October 2015</span> | <a href="/news-11-2015">November 2015</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<p>Welcome to this monthly installment! This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month, and fancontent for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</p>
<h3 id="toc0"><span>On-Site News</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for November are <a href="/scp-1820">SCP-1820</a> (&quot;The Lost Cabin&quot;) by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sarai-seneschal" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1350894); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1350894&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Sarai_Seneschal" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1350894)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sarai-seneschal" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1350894); return false;">Sarai_Seneschal</a></span> and <a href="/world-tour">World Tour</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agatharights" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(232934); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=232934&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="agatharights" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=232934)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agatharights" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(232934); return false;">agatharights</a></span>. One's about a warm, inviting place to stay when you're lost, and the other is about exploring the world and seeing all the wonderful mysteries that hide themselves beneath normalcy. Also, ghosts! Check them out!</li>
<li>The featured articles from October were <a href="/scp-2107">SCP-2107</a> (&quot;Diet Ghost&quot;) by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005876&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Dillinger PhD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005876)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;">Dillinger PhD</a></span> and <a href="/teeth-dearie">Teeth, Dearie</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-loser" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4866573); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4866573&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Dr loser" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4866573)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-loser" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4866573); return false;">Dr loser</a></span>. One's about a soda that's ghostly and made of ghosts, and the other is ghastly and just about your teeth. Give it a bit of a wiggle, maybe? Check them out if you missed them!</li>
<li>No other on-site news for this month, although a reminder that there is a whole list of <a href="/usertools">custom usertools</a> to make your experience on this site better. The most popularly-requested is the Night Mode, released September and available to use. Report any bugs in the article's discussion thread. If you need to look for the page on-hand, there's a link under the User Resources box on the sidebar.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p>Missing out on articles? Enjoy a recap on the articles from the past month, as October has come and gone, and managed to bring us some spooky things!<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup></p>
<h3 id="toc1"><span>Week of October 1st</span></h3>
<p>Not much happened this week. However, we did get some cool stuff. You guys didn't happen to wander into a Halloween store, did you?</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2523">SCP-2523</a> (&quot;Goblin Market&quot;, a rewrite of &quot;Halloween Store&quot;) - From Halloween to November 1st, these stores are full of folklore, merriment, and decoration! Buy spooky stuff, so long as you barter something of yours for it. Go buy your orchard fruits, go buy, go buy! Originally written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/foamfollower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2215314); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2215314&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Foamfollower" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2215314)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/foamfollower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2215314); return false;">Foamfollower</a></span>, whimsically rewritten by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;">sirpudding</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2985">SCP-2985</a> (&quot;Anart, Author of the Scream&quot;) - These paintings are perfect replications&#8230; perhaps too perfect. An artist struggles to get his message heard while bigger players lurk in the shadows. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2038009&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="TyGently" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2038009)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/sunny-art-scp-cards">SunnyClockwork's Artwork - SCP Cards</a> - Ever wanted SCP-themed tarot cards for you and your friends? Look no further than Sunny's art! It's basically what you'd want out of an SCP-themed occult setting, minus the actual ghosts. Created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;">SunnyClockwork</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc2"><span>Week of October 8th</span></h3>
<p>Loads of cool content. These articles are my BFFs.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2286">SCP-2286</a> (&quot;If You Build a Better Mousetrap…&quot;) - If you build an attractor for a mice, you may try it out on people. And if you build an attractor for people&#8230; Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thehermit2" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2006843); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2006843&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="thehermit2" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2006843)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thehermit2" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2006843); return false;">thehermit2</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2790">SCP-2790</a> (&quot;You've Got a Squid in Me&quot;) - Aww, how adorable! We should play and cuddle them! They're so cute, aren't they? Gorgeous skin too. Cutely written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-7394-j">SCP-7394-J</a> (&quot;HILARIOUS FARTING FROG CLICK NOW TO SEE&quot;) - Dude, did you get a load of this frog during lunch break? It let rip this giant, awful fart. We couldn't stop cracking up! #keterfrogfarts courtesy of <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salman-corbette" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(678987); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=678987&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Salman Corbette" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=678987)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salman-corbette" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(678987); return false;">Salman Corbette</a></span> and <a href="/mayreder-personnel-file">Faminepulse</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2298">SCP-2298</a> (&quot;Life in a Plastic Box&quot;) - Go into a shed, and you'll come across a city of mannequins. A closer look shows it's not just a world of fake plastic dummies and fake plastic trees. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eekium" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2137346); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2137346&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Eekium" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2137346)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eekium" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2137346); return false;">Eekium</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2580">SCP-2580</a> (&quot;Father-Daughter Project&quot;) - Father and daughter build a rocket to send to some aliens far off in the galaxy. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zmax15" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000203); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000203&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Zmax15" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000203)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zmax15" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000203); return false;">Zmax15</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2528">SCP-2528</a> (&quot;Panda Processors&quot;) - Computers that see the world change over and over, and no one will listen. All they can do is be trapped and scream. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thamuzz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(830521); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=830521&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="thamuzz" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=830521)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thamuzz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(830521); return false;">thamuzz</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/document-48116-88-son-of-the-earth">Document 48116-88 (&quot;Son of the Earth&quot;)</a> - My dearest Mashen'ka, I hope you and him are happy together, for these lost words are all I am able to offer again. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/blackbird5154" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2074508); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2074508&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Blackbird5154" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2074508)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/blackbird5154" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2074508); return false;">Blackbird5154</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/iavev" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1802509); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1802509&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="iavev" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1802509)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/iavev" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1802509); return false;">iavev</a></span>, translated by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gene-r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(634139); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=634139&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Gene R" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=634139)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gene-r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(634139); return false;">Gene R</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/a-witch-s-tale-mistakes-were-made">A Witch's Tale - Mistakes Were Made</a> - The cost of art is nothing compared to the message it'll send&#8230; or so they'll tell you. Take it from a witch; God hates art. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;">sirpudding</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a class="newpage" href="/dreamwalkerfae-s-author-page">DreamwalkerFae's Author Page</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hotcocoanerd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2032511); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2032511&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="HotCocoaNerd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2032511)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hotcocoanerd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2032511); return false;">HotCocoaNerd</a></span>'s author page! Greetings o' weary traveler. Come in, and sit down, and let Fae weave you a story about those who lived on.</li>
<li><a href="/circlesandsquares-author-page">CirclesAndSquares Author Page</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/circlesandsquares" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1367458); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1367458&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="CirclesAndSquares" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1367458)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/circlesandsquares" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1367458); return false;">CirclesAndSquares</a></span>' author page! Though, uh, someone should look into Dr. Bessette's unusual behavior.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc3"><span>Week of October 15th</span></h3>
<p>If you're feeling sinister, go off and see your minister&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2459">SCP-2459</a> (&quot;When the Traffic Clears&quot;) - These are all my possessions, and I can't just leave them. Would you walk up and away from all you hold dear or believe in? Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;">WrongJohnSilver</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2741">SCP-2741</a> (&quot;A Sinister Device&quot;) - A HA HA HA HA HA! ARE YOU READY TO FEEL&#8230; SINISTER? READ THE ARTICLE WHEN READY, AND THINGS WILL BECOME TRULY… SINISTER!! Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/freudian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(619549); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=619549&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Freudian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=619549)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/freudian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(619549); return false;">Freudian</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2106">SCP-2106</a> (&quot;A Conspiracy of Ravens&quot;) - The ravens flock together to feel human again. The human feels like a raven. This dynamic is too delicate to disturb. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1372582&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Jacob Conwell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1372582)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;">Jacob Conwell</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2428">SCP-2428</a> (&quot;Mr. Mad&quot;) - Sanity is relative. And in the wacky world of Wondertainment, Mr. Mad is the odd one out. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2910">SCP-2910</a> (&quot;Welt am Draht&quot;) - Ever feel like people are ignoring you on purpose? They are. Forever. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/home-again">Home Again</a> - &quot;&quot;As I looked through the lens, the light…the flowers…the soldier returning to his lover after a deployment in hell…all of it suddenly felt perfect.&quot; Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/snarky-potato" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2278967); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2278967&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Snarky Potato" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2278967)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/snarky-potato" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2278967); return false;">Snarky Potato</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/a-swingsets-song">A Swingset's Song</a> - I failed three times, abysmal; alone and guilty, tragic, Knowing that my ledger's full; red from misuse, magic. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/researcher-dios" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2374027); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2374027&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="researcher-dios" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2374027)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/researcher-dios" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2374027); return false;">researcher-dios</a></span>, but you'll probably forget about it.</li>
<li><a href="/fear-not">Fear Not</a> - &quot;Do you understand literary allusion and quantum mechanics? Neither does anyone else, that's why this is still only +18.&quot; The previous blurb definitely not written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1379080&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Randomini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1379080)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span> or anything, but the tale was.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc4"><span>Week of October 22nd</span></h3>
<p>Some clockworks and flesh walk into a bar.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-300-j">SCP-300-J</a> - Do you think puns rule? You probably can't measure how much you may or may not hate them. Miles-ly irritating as well. Probably written with a straight face by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/swaghetti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2139646); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2139646&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Swaghetti" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2139646)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/swaghetti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2139646); return false;">Swaghetti</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-723-j">SCP-723-J</a> (&quot;Sad Roach&quot;) - Sad roach is sad. I wonder what happened to that roach to make it so sad. It must have had a hard life. Sadness transcribed by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404533&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Zyn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404533)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;">Zyn</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/silberescher" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304355); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=304355&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Silberescher" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=304355)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/silberescher" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304355); return false;">Silberescher</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2967">SCP-2967</a> (&quot;Australian Selkie&quot;) - Sometimes, conspiracies show in the weirdest and innocuous forms. You ever seen a seal before? Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/freudian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(619549); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=619549&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Freudian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=619549)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/freudian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(619549); return false;">Freudian</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2509">SCP-2509</a> (&quot;Hardware Pets&quot;) - Aww, cute pets! Don't act out-of-control now&#8230; hey, hey! Don't whir that blade that close to me! Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/circlesandsquares" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1367458); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1367458&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="CirclesAndSquares" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1367458)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/circlesandsquares" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1367458); return false;">CirclesAndSquares</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2168">SCP-2168</a> (&quot;Progress&quot;) - The progress always moves forward, changing, transforming and destroying. Do you desire to stay for an easier life of slavery or go away, escape, marked forever? Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aleph-a" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2200530); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2200530&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Aleph_A" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2200530)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aleph-a" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2200530); return false;">Aleph_A</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/hallowinside">Hallow Inside</a> - A Broken God member and a Sakricst priest trick-or-treat for Halloween, and find time to make some awkward talk. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hatismyfriend" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2172859); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2172859&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="HatIsMyFriend" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2172859)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hatismyfriend" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2172859); return false;">HatIsMyFriend</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/freudian">Dr Jung's Terminal</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/freudian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(619549); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=619549&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Freudian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=619549)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/freudian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(619549); return false;">Freudian</a></span>'s author page! Dr. Jung is away, but leave him an email and he may get back to you in a timely manner.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc5"><span>Week of October 29th</span></h3>
<p>Spooky scary skeletons.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2944">SCP-2944</a> (&quot;An Anomalous Haircut&quot;) - It is, indeed, an anomalous haircut. A pretty ugly one, if you ask me. Is it worth it to control all the hairs on your body? Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cavalry" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2210946); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2210946&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Cavalry " style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2210946)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cavalry" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2210946); return false;">Cavalry</a></span> .</li>
<li><a href="/scp-512">SCP-512</a> (&quot;Gravity-Nullifying Umbrella&quot;) - A rewrite of the <a href="http://scpclassic.wikidot.com/scp-512">old 512</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hk-016" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172931); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=172931&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="HK-016" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=172931)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hk-016" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172931); return false;">HK-016</a></span>. Poor Mary Poppins, to say the least. Brought back to life by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1229263&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Roget" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1229263)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;">Roget</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dexanote" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(481882); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=481882&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Dexanote" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=481882)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dexanote" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(481882); return false;">Dexanote</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2263">SCP-2263</a> (&quot;The Skeleton Gallery&quot;) - A gallery full of skeletons, and an artist determined to put make them stand out. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-solo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1476008); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1476008&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Dr Solo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1476008)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-solo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1476008); return false;">Dr Solo</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc6"><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h3>
<p>What's been going on in the community aside from our site? Well&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://scpfoundation.ru/site-7-midnight-radio">Site 7 Midnight Radio</a> - A podcast hosted by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/blackbird5154" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2074508); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2074508&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Blackbird5154" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2074508)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/blackbird5154" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2074508); return false;">Blackbird5154</a></span> and technical help and publishing done by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/iavev" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1802509); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1802509&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="iavev" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1802509)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/iavev" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1802509); return false;">iavev</a></span> over on the Russian site! If you understand Russian and wanna take a look, feel free. Be sure to inform us of what they say too!</li>
<li>ZAP has created <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CjG0lJ_p0Xw">SCP MOVIE: Episode 1</a>, a well-shot, tensely-filmed, and atmospheric video about <a href="/scp-004">SCP-004</a>. It's in Russian, but with English subtitles, so you can enjoy it!</li>
<li>This Exists, a YouTube channel pointing out and explaining cool pop culture stuff, did a video on the SCP Wiki! The <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=55igYZ0EShc">video</a> is short and succinct, and while it doesn't cover everything, it's a great entry video for those new.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Daily_SCP/">Daily_SCP</a> is a subreddit that showcases a new SCP a day, from the well-known to the obscure and hidden. A good way to find new skips you may not have heard of; I know I've discovered a couple new favorites from it. It's run by user HighlyDestruct7.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1414320">SCP Minecraft</a> yet again rises from the grave! Servers are run by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1414765&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1589572990" alt="Doctor Cimmerian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1414765)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;">Doctor Cimmerian</a></span>, check it out!</li>
</ul>
<p>Come back next month when there's more articles and content your way! This is a new feature, so let me know what you think, if the standards for showcasing should be greater (this showcased articles with a rating higher than +10<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-2')">2</a></sup>), what fancontent I've missed, etc. I'd be happy to make this better for you guys! :)</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
